The paper deals with the time and space complexity of the $k$-SUM problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science related to data structures, computational geometry, and complexity theory. Therefore, it is likely to be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper presents a reduction technique that has implications for information theory, which could lead to a classification under cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
